9 SECTION 2. A new section of the Liquor Excise Tax Act,
10 Section 7-17-5.2 NMSA 1978, is enacted to read:
11 "7-17-5.2. [NEW MATERIAL] IMPOSITION AND RATE OF LIQUOR
12 EXCISE SURTAX.--Beginning July 1, 2027, there is imposed on a
13 retailer that sells alcoholic beverages not for resale an
14 excise surtax, to be referred to as the "liquor excise surtax",
15 at the rate of three percent of the price paid for alcoholic
16 beverages sold by the retailer."
17 SECTION 3. Section 7-17-6 NMSA 1978 (being Laws 1984,
